<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-28T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-28T02:00:00-05:00" n="886" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">800.0146/8–2844: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-28T14:00:00+07:00">August 28,
                                1944—2 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received August 28—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1464. Soong asked me on August 24 for information as to progress in regard to
                        suggested three-power conference on the question of administration of
                        liberated areas in Far East (ReEmbs 1289, July 25 and ReDepts 1036, August
                        3).</p>
                    <p>Soong asked me to inquire on progress and said he attached importance to
                        early development of this matter. It is probable that Generalissimo is
                        presses [<hi rend="italic">pressing</hi>] him in regard to it.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>